[normal]A[bold]ppendix[bold] A[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Terms of Reference for the Advisory Committee on the Safety of Blood,[bold]Tissues and Organs (SaBTO)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]The Committee will advise Ministers of the UK Government and the Devolved Administrations as well as UK Health Departments on the most appropriate ways to ensure the safety of blood, cells, tissues and organs for transfusion / transplantation. Its remit includes providing advice on the microbiological safety of gametes and stem cells, in liaison with the relevant regulatory authorities. The Committee will provide independent advice on risk management for Ministers and UK Health Departments to consider.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In formulating its advice, the Committee will:
